### Cloud Cost Optimizer — sample API calls
### Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension, or translate to curl.
### Base URL assumes: uvicorn app.main:app  (http://127.0.0.1:8000)

@base = http://127.0.0.1:8000

### Health check
GET {{base}}/health

### Open the dashboard (HTML) in a browser
GET {{base}}/

### 1. Scan the sample CUR -> detect waste -> persist (no enrichment)
POST {{base}}/scan
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 1b. Scan AND run the LLM enrichment layer in one call
POST {{base}}/scan
Content-Type: application/json

{ "enrich": true }

### 2. List all findings (sorted by risk score, highest first)
GET {{base}}/findings

### 2b. Filter findings by type
GET {{base}}/findings?finding_type=unattached_ebs_volume

### 2c. Filter findings by risk bucket
GET {{base}}/findings?risk_bucket=Medium

### 3. Enrich a scan's findings (cached per finding type)
POST {{base}}/enrich/1

### 4. Propose remediation (DEFAULT = dry-run, nothing executes)
POST {{base}}/remediate/1
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 4b. Request real remediation WITHOUT confirmation -> status "proposed"
POST {{base}}/remediate/1
Content-Type: application/json

{ "dry_run": false, "confirm": false }

### 4c. Confirmed remediation -> validated + allowlisted, but NOT executed ($0 / no live cloud)
POST {{base}}/remediate/1
Content-Type: application/json

{ "dry_run": false, "confirm": true }
